<section xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="SshdLogLevel" version="5.0">
  <title xml:id="RemoteAccessServices">SSHD Logging Level</title>
  <para>
  Configures the secure shell (SSH) daemon's logging level.
 </para>
  <para>
  Acceptable logging levels are 'QUIET', 'FATAL', 'ERROR', 'INFO',
  'VERBOSE', 'DEBUG', 'DEBUG1', 'DEBUG2', and 'DEBUG3'. Most guidelines
  recommend the logging level be set to 'VERBOSE'.
 </para>
